Liverpool Captain Gerrard to Miss Start of Season With Infection

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-30T12:28:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-30/liverpool-captain-gerrard-to-miss-start-of-season-with-infection.html
Liverpool captain  Steven Gerrard 
will miss the start of the Premier League season after being
admitted to the hospital with an infection related to a groin
injury.  Gerrard is expected to remain in the hospital for “several
days” while he completes an antibiotic treatement, Liverpool
said on its website. He’s not expected to play until September,
the club said.  Gerrard will miss Liverpool’s first three games against
Sunderland, Arsenal and Bolton. His return may come in the Reds’
game at Stoke on Sept. 10.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  